This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it proposes a new quality link metric for wireless multi-hop networks. It also considers the impact of MAC layer on link performance and route quality, which is a key aspect of network and internet architecture. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bandwidth sharing mechanism of 802.11, which is a common protocol used in network and internet architecture. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the calculation of interference and bandwidth, which are important aspects of information theory. 

Furthermore, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM) as wireless multi-hop networks are often used for multimedia applications such as video streaming and audio transmission. 

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as wireless multi-hop networks are vulnerable to security threats such as eavesdropping and data tampering. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it proposes a new metric for selecting routes in wireless multi-hop networks, which is a control problem.
